❓ 1. What happens internally when you run a Spring Boot app?

👉 Answer:
@SpringBootApplication triggers:
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan
Spring Boot:
Creates ApplicationContext
Scans beans
Applies auto-configuration
Starts embedded server (Tomcat)

🧠 Smart line:
👉 “Spring Boot bootstraps the application by auto-configuring beans and starting an embedded server.”
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
❓ 2. Difference: @Component vs @Bean (very tricky)

👉 Answer:
@Component	                  @Bean
Auto-detected	               Manually defined
Class-level	                 Method-level
Used for your classes	       Used for third-party classes

🧠 Example:
@Component → your service
@Bean → ObjectMapper, DataSource
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
❓ 3. What is AutoConfiguration? How does it work?
👉 Answer: Spring Boot automatically configures beans based on:
Classpath
Properties
Conditions

👉 Uses:
@ConditionalOnClass
@ConditionalOnMissingBean

🧠 Example:
If MySQL dependency present → DataSource auto-configured
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

❓ 4. What if two beans of same type exist?
👉 Answer: Spring throws:  NoUniqueBeanDefinitionException
👉 Solution: @Primary , @Qualifier
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
❓ 5. @RestController vs @Controller

👉 Answer:
@Controller → returns view (HTML)
@RestController → returns JSON

👉 Internally:
@RestController = @Controller + @ResponseBody
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
❓ 6. How does Spring Boot handle dependency injection?
👉 Answer:
Using IoC container

Types:
Constructor injection ✅ (best)
Setter injection
Field injection ❌ (not recommended)

🧠 Why constructor?
👉 Immutable + testable
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
